So we visited Cage Luluc today, it was my son's Birthday , he turned 15 so we had lunch. Our son have severe allegies so we are very picky about where we eat. I got him his favorite gluten free vegan cake from the city and then drove to Cafe Luluc. Whe we got there we were seated, and I asked the host if she could please put our tiny cake in the fridge for us because it would melt in the heat while we ate. She said sure, yes Happy Birthday! I went to wash my hands and notice she was standing there with the box in her hand when we I came out the restroom. She proceeded to tell me that to cut our cake they charge $15 dollars, so I said well we're not  cutting the cake here, I just would like it refrigerated so it doesn't melt, while we ate. She took the cake to the back and brought it back to us and said..oh we don't have space..A tiny cake? I mean you certainly were going to find space for $15 to cut  it right, but then when you learned you weren't making that extra $15, you suddenly don't have space? How convenient Cafe Luluc. This is very distasteful of you, and shame on you..You ruined my son's Birthday cake because of your insensitivity..When we bought the cake home to celebrate at home, the whole cake melted..This is terrible.You will never see another dollar of ours  again. You should be thankful that you still have a business for people to come to, when many other businesses have closed due to covid..Be humble, be grateful, show gratitude, be good to the remaining guest that you have coming in your establishment, because in the blink of an eye it could all be gone..Look around at the sign of the times..Horrible Horrible!!! Never again.
